subsection.text:

  Section 216(h)(1)(A)(i) of the Social Security Act (
  42 U.S.C. 416(h)(1)(A)(i)
) is amended by striking is domiciled and all that follows through the District of Columbia, and inserting and such applicant were married (or, if such insured individual and such applicant were not married in any State but were validly married in another jurisdiction, the courts of any State).
